						<summary>

						<p>Broken stone lying on a raised pial near the Bhaṇḍāri-kēri-maṭha.</p>						

						<p>Circa 14th century.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary record seems to register a gift of land and money, for offerings and burning a perpetual lamp probably in a <hi rend="italic">maṭha</hi> by Tirumakaṁbaḷi and Saṅkuseṭi. The gift was entrusted to Raghuvara-tīrtha-śrīpāda. <hi rend="italic">Karaṇika</hi> Mallarasa of Bārakūru wrote the record.</p>						

						</summary>
